WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:01:54.614 --> 00:01:55.647
         (GRUNTS)

3
00:01:57.918 --> 00:02:00.769
   Out. all of you.

4
00:02:02.573 --> 00:02:05.974
 This bastard's been meddling
 where he shouldn't!

5
00:02:06.042 --> 00:02:08.893
 I want you and your men

6
00:02:10.263 --> 00:02:11.262
 gone.

7
00:02:13.233 --> 00:02:15.333
 And you will make this right.

8
00:02:15.402 --> 00:02:16.502
       (SPITS)

9
00:02:18.572 --> 00:02:19.755
         Wait outside.

10
00:02:19.840 --> 00:02:21.640
 Lord Commander...
              Now!

11
00:02:28.949 --> 00:02:30.182
             (SIGHS)

12
00:02:42.162 --> 00:02:43.144
            Lord Commander...

13
00:02:43.213 --> 00:02:44.245
           Leave us.

14
00:02:46.283 --> 00:02:47.849
     What did you do?

15
00:02:48.652 --> 00:02:50.786
     I followed him.

16
00:02:50.854 --> 00:02:53.154
 He took the baby
 into the woods. the newborn.

17
00:02:53.223 --> 00:02:54.923
            What business
            is that of yours?

18
00:02:54.992 --> 00:02:56.558
 No. you don't understand.

19
00:02:56.627 --> 00:02:58.961
 He's killing them.
 all the boys.

20
00:03:04.651 --> 00:03:05.867
         You know.

21
00:03:09.540 --> 00:03:13.841
    Wildlings serve
    crueler gods than you or I.

22
00:03:15.579 --> 00:03:19.064
           Those boys are
           Craster's offerings.

23
00:03:19.132 --> 00:03:20.432
      Offerings?

24
00:03:20.500 --> 00:03:22.668
    He's murdering
    his own children.
    He's a monster.

25
00:03:22.736 --> 00:03:25.170
            Aye. many a time
            that monster has
            been the difference

26
00:03:25.238 --> 00:03:27.606
        between life and
        death for our rangers.

27
00:03:27.675 --> 00:03:29.575
         your uncle among them.

28
00:03:30.611 --> 00:03:34.279
            We have other wars
            to fight out there.

29
00:03:34.347 --> 00:03:38.116
      Like it or not.
      we need men like Craster.

30
00:03:43.390 --> 00:03:44.623
          I...

31
00:03:45.059 --> 00:03:46.491
        I saw it.

32
00:03:49.496 --> 00:03:50.896
         I saw

33
00:03:53.166 --> 00:03:55.433
 something take that child.

34
00:03:56.536 --> 00:04:00.538
         Yeah. Whatever it was.

35
00:04:00.608 --> 00:04:02.240
           I daresay
           you'll see it again.

36
00:04:04.645 --> 00:04:07.613
           Now. ready my horse.

37
00:04:07.681 --> 00:04:09.547
              We leave at dawn.

38
00:04:15.155 --> 00:04:17.055
           Don't lose it again.

39
00:04:24.831 --> 00:04:26.030
         (MEN SHOUTING)

40
00:04:26.099 --> 00:04:27.231
       (BIRDS SQUAWKING)

41
00:04:41.348 --> 00:04:42.764
                 Gilly.

42
00:04:46.052 --> 00:04:48.253
 You're leaving.

43
00:04:48.322 --> 00:04:51.390
           I... I wanted to
           give you something.

44
00:04:55.812 --> 00:04:57.779
      It belonged to my mother.

45
00:04:59.717 --> 00:05:00.749
 I can't take it.

46
00:05:00.818 --> 00:05:02.300
                      Please.

47
00:05:02.369 --> 00:05:03.968
             I want you to.

48
00:05:07.341 --> 00:05:10.208
  My mother used it for sewing.

49
00:05:10.276 --> 00:05:14.245
        She'd let me sit
        with her in her chamber
        while she sewed

50
00:05:14.314 --> 00:05:15.596
           and I'd read to her.

51
00:05:18.552 --> 00:05:21.553
       My father put a stop
       to it when he found out.

52
00:05:23.006 --> 00:05:25.941
            It's the only thing
            I have of hers.

53
00:05:26.009 --> 00:05:28.743
    She gave it to me
    before I left for the Wall.

54
00:05:30.046 --> 00:05:31.379
        You...

55
00:05:31.447 --> 00:05:32.781
 You shouldn't give it away.

56
00:05:32.849 --> 00:05:34.749
        I'm not giving it away.

57
00:05:36.486 --> 00:05:37.736
          I'm giving it to you.

58
00:05:40.473 --> 00:05:42.273
           Keep it safe for me.

59
00:05:43.210 --> 00:05:44.892
             Till I come back.

60
00:05:53.970 --> 00:05:55.437
        (GOATS BLEATING)

61
00:05:55.505 --> 00:05:57.271
         (WOLF PANTING)

62
00:06:03.179 --> 00:06:04.713
                Hodor.

63
00:06:04.781 --> 00:06:06.715
          Hodor.

64
00:06:06.783 --> 00:06:09.918
 Rouse Bran. will you?
 It's time for his lessons.

65
00:06:31.108 --> 00:06:32.273
             (GASPS)

66
00:06:35.512 --> 00:06:37.111
       (BREATHING HEAVILY)

67
00:06:42.403 --> 00:06:44.436
     BRAN:
     Every night it's the same.

68
00:06:45.688 --> 00:06:47.155
              I'm walking

69
00:06:47.757 --> 00:06:49.590
            and running. but...

70
00:06:52.029 --> 00:06:54.496
         I'm not... I'm not me.

71
00:06:56.266 --> 00:06:57.965
          I'm running
          through the godswood.

72
00:06:58.035 --> 00:07:00.435
             sniffing the dirt.

73
00:07:00.504 --> 00:07:03.571
   tasting blood in my mouth
   when I've made a fresh kill.

74
00:07:04.807 --> 00:07:06.207
                    howling.

75
00:07:08.595 --> 00:07:10.796
                Old Nan used to
                tell me stories

76
00:07:10.864 --> 00:07:12.831
           about magical people
           who could live

77
00:07:12.900 --> 00:07:15.684
           inside stags. birds.

78
00:07:16.319 --> 00:07:17.652
                   wolves.

79
00:07:17.721 --> 00:07:19.570
 That's exactly
 what they are. Bran.

80
00:07:20.140 --> 00:07:21.272
      stories.

81
00:07:21.341 --> 00:07:22.407
              So she was lying?

82
00:07:22.476 --> 00:07:24.109
              They don't exist?

83
00:07:24.177 --> 00:07:25.743
 Well. they may have done.

84
00:07:25.812 --> 00:07:28.513
 But they're gone
 from the world.

85
00:07:28.582 --> 00:07:30.582
 along with much else.

86
00:07:32.285 --> 00:07:35.886
 These are dreams.
 Bran. nothing more.

87
00:07:35.955 --> 00:07:38.856
   No. my dreams are different.

88
00:07:38.925 --> 00:07:40.558
                 Mine are true.

89
00:07:40.627 --> 00:07:42.944
   I dreamt of my father dying.

90
00:07:44.180 --> 00:07:45.980
 And Rickon had the same dream.

91
00:07:46.049 --> 00:07:48.867
 What about all
 the dreams you had
 that didn't come true?

92
00:07:51.004 --> 00:07:52.337
           Hmm?

93
00:07:55.208 --> 00:07:56.474
   (CLEARS THROAT)

94
00:07:56.543 --> 00:07:58.442
      Right.

95
00:07:58.511 --> 00:08:02.680
 This link is made
 of Valyrian steel.

96
00:08:02.749 --> 00:08:06.817
 Only one maester in 100
 wears it on his chain.

97
00:08:06.886 --> 00:08:10.605
 It signifies that I have
 studied the higher mysteries.

98
00:08:10.673 --> 00:08:14.909
 And all who
 study these mysteries
 try their hand at spells.

99
00:08:14.978 --> 00:08:17.011
 I was no different.

100
00:08:17.080 --> 00:08:19.013
    I was young.

101
00:08:19.082 --> 00:08:23.518
 And what boy doesn't secretly
 wish for hidden powers

102
00:08:23.587 --> 00:08:26.921
 to lift him out
 of his dull life
 into a special one?

103
00:08:28.024 --> 00:08:30.291
 But in the end.
 for all my efforts.

104
00:08:30.360 --> 00:08:33.694
 I got no more out of it
 than a thousand
 boys before me.

105
00:08:33.763 --> 00:08:36.464
 (CHUCKLES) Come on.

106
00:08:44.975 --> 00:08:47.541
    All right.

107
00:08:47.610 --> 00:08:51.212
 Maybe magic once was
 a mighty force in the world.

108
00:08:53.749 --> 00:08:55.316
 But not anymore.

109
00:08:57.287 --> 00:08:59.487
 The dragons are gone.

110
00:08:59.555 --> 00:09:01.289
 The giants are dead.

111
00:09:03.593 --> 00:09:06.427
 And the Children of
 the Forest forgotten.

112
00:09:09.416 --> 00:09:11.316
               (SIGHS)

113
00:09:16.890 --> 00:09:17.989
         (MEN CHEERING)

114
00:09:18.058 --> 00:09:19.073
      (GRUNTING)

115
00:09:28.368 --> 00:09:29.600
               (GRUNTS)

116
00:09:29.669 --> 00:09:30.951
         (MEN SHOUTING)

117
00:09:56.680 --> 00:09:58.346
             Loras! Highgarden!

118
00:10:03.470 --> 00:10:04.618
           Get him!

119
00:10:06.006 --> 00:10:07.021
                 (GASPS)

120
00:10:07.807 --> 00:10:09.040
      (GRUNTS)

121
00:10:09.109 --> 00:10:10.275
           CROWD: Oh!

122
00:10:12.295 --> 00:10:14.745
         Yield! I yield.

123
00:10:23.940 --> 00:10:26.090
              Well fought.
              Approach.

124
00:10:35.735 --> 00:10:37.685
       Rise. Remove your helm.

125
00:10:41.057 --> 00:10:42.690
       (CROWD MURMURING)

126
00:10:46.479 --> 00:10:49.547
         You are all your
         father promised
         and more. my lady.

127
00:10:49.615 --> 00:10:51.816
        I've seen Ser Loras
        bested once or twice.

128
00:10:51.885 --> 00:10:54.435
          but never quite
          in that fashion.

129
00:10:54.503 --> 00:10:57.972
             Now. now. my love.
             My brother fought
             valiantly for you.

130
00:10:59.409 --> 00:11:01.609
        That he did.
        my queen.

131
00:11:01.677 --> 00:11:04.178
      But there can
      only be one champion.

132
00:11:05.081 --> 00:11:06.680
      Brienne of Tarth.

133
00:11:06.750 --> 00:11:08.816
    you may ask
    anything of me you desire.

134
00:11:08.885 --> 00:11:11.552
      If it is within my power.
      it is yours.

135
00:11:13.590 --> 00:11:15.557
              Your Grace.

136
00:11:15.625 --> 00:11:18.859
    I ask the honor of
    a place in your Kingsguard.

137
00:11:18.928 --> 00:11:20.478
       (CROWD MURMURING)
         What?

138
00:11:20.547 --> 00:11:23.231
   I will be one of your seven.
   pledge my life to yours.

139
00:11:23.300 --> 00:11:25.466
             and keep you safe
             from all harm.

140
00:11:30.173 --> 00:11:31.172
                  Done.

141
00:11:32.291 --> 00:11:34.325
     Rise.
     Brienne of the Kingsguard.

142
00:11:43.587 --> 00:11:46.788
 Your Grace. I have
 the honor to bring
 you Lady Catelyn Stark.

143
00:11:46.857 --> 00:11:49.908
  sent as an envoy
  by her son Robb.
  Lord of Winterfell.

144
00:11:49.976 --> 00:11:53.645
         Lord of Winterfell
         and King in the North.

145
00:11:53.713 --> 00:11:57.214
        Lady Catelyn.
        I'm pleased to see you.

146
00:11:57.283 --> 00:12:00.434
   May I present my wife.
   Margaery of House Tyrell?

147
00:12:01.855 --> 00:12:04.522
      You are very
      welcome here. Lady Stark.

148
00:12:04.591 --> 00:12:06.157
    I'm so sorry for your loss.

149
00:12:07.644 --> 00:12:09.410
            You are most kind.

150
00:12:09.479 --> 00:12:11.880
             RENLY: My lady.

151
00:12:11.948 --> 00:12:15.650
     I swear to you I will
     see the Lannisters answer
     for your husband's murder.

152
00:12:16.903 --> 00:12:19.487
    When I take King's Landing.

153
00:12:19.556 --> 00:12:21.289
 I'll bring you Joffrey's head.

154
00:12:21.357 --> 00:12:22.590
           (CHEERING)

155
00:12:30.032 --> 00:12:33.434
     It will be enough
     to know that
     justice was done. my lord.

156
00:12:33.503 --> 00:12:35.570
           BRIENNE: Your Grace.

157
00:12:35.655 --> 00:12:37.955
    And you should kneel
    when you approach the King.

158
00:12:38.024 --> 00:12:41.292
      There's no need for that.
      Lady Stark is
      an honored guest.

159
00:12:41.360 --> 00:12:45.196
   Has your son marched against
   Tywin Lannister yet?

160
00:12:45.265 --> 00:12:47.865
           I do not sit on my
           son's war councils.

161
00:12:47.934 --> 00:12:52.003
          And if I did.
          I would not share his
          strategies with you.

162
00:12:52.071 --> 00:12:55.039
 If Robb Stark
 wants a pact with us.
 he should come himself.

163
00:12:55.108 --> 00:12:56.758
 not hide behind
 his mother's skirts.

164
00:12:56.843 --> 00:13:01.879
      My son is fighting a war.
      not playing at one.

165
00:13:01.948 --> 00:13:03.431
        (MEN GRUMBLING)

166
00:13:04.634 --> 00:13:06.017
               (CHUCKLES)

167
00:13:15.178 --> 00:13:17.212
      Don't worry. my lady.

168
00:13:17.280 --> 00:13:19.347
    Our war is just beginning.

169
00:13:26.589 --> 00:13:28.088
         (MEN SHOUTING)

170
00:13:32.995 --> 00:13:34.495
      Your Grace.
                        Gerard.

171
00:13:34.563 --> 00:13:35.863
               How's your foot?

172
00:13:35.932 --> 00:13:37.464
 Better. Your Grace.

173
00:13:37.533 --> 00:13:39.566
 They don't know
 their own size is all.

174
00:13:39.635 --> 00:13:41.068
                  Good man.

175
00:13:43.439 --> 00:13:45.739
          I have 100.000 men
          at my command.

176
00:13:45.808 --> 00:13:48.042
 All the might
 of the Stormlands
 and the Reach.

177
00:13:48.111 --> 00:13:51.845
 And all of them young and bold
 like your Knight of Flowers?

178
00:13:52.715 --> 00:13:55.349
 It's a game to you. isn't it?

179
00:13:55.418 --> 00:13:56.417
  I pity them.

180
00:13:56.485 --> 00:13:57.484
                    Why?

181
00:13:57.553 --> 00:13:59.287
 Because it won't last.

182
00:13:59.355 --> 00:14:03.090
 Because they are
 the knights of summer
 and winter is coming.

183
00:14:05.328 --> 00:14:08.463
           Brienne. escort Lady
           Catelyn to her tent.

184
00:14:09.632 --> 00:14:11.099
  She's tired from her journey.

185
00:14:11.167 --> 00:14:12.616
  BRIENNE: At once. Your Grace.

186
00:14:12.669 --> 00:14:13.835
          Shall I return after?

187
00:14:13.903 --> 00:14:15.202
  That won't be necessary.

188
00:14:15.271 --> 00:14:17.638
       I would pray awhile.
       Alone.

189
00:14:19.775 --> 00:14:21.392
  If you'll follow me. my lady.

190
00:14:24.431 --> 00:14:27.599
 You fought bravely today.
 Lady Brienne.

191
00:14:27.667 --> 00:14:29.800
          I fought for my king.

192
00:14:29.869 --> 00:14:32.503
        Soon I'll fight for him
        on the battlefield.

193
00:14:32.572 --> 00:14:35.340
         Die for him if I must.

194
00:14:35.408 --> 00:14:38.543
         And. if it please you.
         Brienne's enough.

195
00:14:39.912 --> 00:14:41.346
                 I'm no lady.

196
00:15:12.745 --> 00:15:14.895
 What are you doing here?

197
00:15:14.964 --> 00:15:16.914
           I live here.

198
00:15:16.983 --> 00:15:19.600
          Are you angry
          with me. brother?

199
00:15:19.669 --> 00:15:21.052
 You lying bitch.

200
00:15:21.120 --> 00:15:24.321
          It's not my fault you
          didn't recognize me.

201
00:15:24.390 --> 00:15:27.191
 Recognize you? How could I?

202
00:15:27.260 --> 00:15:28.993
 The last time I saw you...

203
00:15:31.030 --> 00:15:32.930
     you looked like
     a fat little boy.

204
00:15:34.033 --> 00:15:36.634
              You were a fat
              little boy. too.

205
00:15:36.703 --> 00:15:38.852
          but I recognized you.

206
00:15:38.939 --> 00:15:40.371
 Why didn't you tell me?

207
00:15:40.440 --> 00:15:42.423
            I wanted to see
            who you were first.

208
00:15:43.092 --> 00:15:44.241
         (LAUGHS) And I did.

209
00:15:47.163 --> 00:15:49.663
 The plans are made.
 It's time you heard them.

210
00:15:49.732 --> 00:15:51.649
                        Father.
            Father.

211
00:15:54.236 --> 00:15:56.437
 The wolf pup has gone south

212
00:15:56.505 --> 00:15:59.640
 with the entirety
 of the Northern
 army at his back.

213
00:15:59.709 --> 00:16:02.476
 While he's tangling with
 the lion in the Westerlands.

214
00:16:02.545 --> 00:16:05.496
 the North is
 ripe for the taking.

215
00:16:05.564 --> 00:16:08.682
 The ironborn will
 reave and pillage.
 as it was in the old days.

216
00:16:08.751 --> 00:16:11.051
 all along the northern coast.

217
00:16:11.120 --> 00:16:13.988
 We'll spread our dominion
 across the green lands.

218
00:16:14.057 --> 00:16:16.874
 securing the Neck
 and everything above.

219
00:16:16.926 --> 00:16:19.727
    Every stronghold
    will yield to us.
    one by one.

220
00:16:19.796 --> 00:16:22.646
 Winterfell may
 defy us for a year.
 but what of it?

221
00:16:22.715 --> 00:16:24.432
 The rest shall be ours.

222
00:16:24.501 --> 00:16:27.518
 forest. field. and hall.

223
00:16:32.291 --> 00:16:35.009
 Yara. my daughter.
 you'll take 30 longships

224
00:16:35.077 --> 00:16:36.878
 to attack Deepwood Motte.

225
00:16:36.946 --> 00:16:39.113
 I've always wanted a castle.

226
00:16:39.181 --> 00:16:42.966
             And what's my role
             in all this?

227
00:16:43.036 --> 00:16:46.888
 You'll take a ship to raid
 the fishing villages
 on the Stoney Shore.

228
00:16:46.956 --> 00:16:48.656
                    A ship?

229
00:16:48.724 --> 00:16:50.724
                You give her 30
                and I get one?

230
00:16:50.794 --> 00:16:54.078
 The Sea Bitch.
 We thought she'd
 be perfect for you.

231
00:16:56.733 --> 00:16:58.082
        I'm to fight fishermen?

232
00:16:58.150 --> 00:17:00.184
 Be careful of their nets.

233
00:17:03.606 --> 00:17:07.942
      Father.
      I fought with Robb Stark.
      I know his men.

234
00:17:08.011 --> 00:17:09.359
 He won't give up
 the North so easily.

235
00:17:09.428 --> 00:17:10.795
              They won't even
              know we're there

236
00:17:10.863 --> 00:17:12.563
           until it's too late.
 What do you know of it. woman?

237
00:17:12.631 --> 00:17:14.065
 I'm a proven warrior.

238
00:17:14.133 --> 00:17:17.417
   Your brothers were warriors.
   both of them dead

239
00:17:17.486 --> 00:17:20.904
  at the hands of those
  you seem so eager to protect.

240
00:17:23.025 --> 00:17:24.758
 I'm not protecting anyone.

241
00:17:24.827 --> 00:17:26.828
 I just wonder if
 it's not wiser to wait.

242
00:17:26.896 --> 00:17:30.965
 Why risk going
 against the North
 if they would be our allies?

243
00:17:31.033 --> 00:17:33.267
 Rise up against them
 and they could destroy us.

244
00:17:33.336 --> 00:17:36.003
 But if we pledge
 fealty to them.

245
00:17:36.072 --> 00:17:37.671
 they'll give us Casterly Rock.

246
00:17:37.740 --> 00:17:39.506
            What are our words?

247
00:17:41.093 --> 00:17:42.576
                   Our words?

248
00:17:45.565 --> 00:17:46.597
   We do not sow.

249
00:17:46.665 --> 00:17:48.232
                We do not sow.

250
00:17:48.301 --> 00:17:49.934
               We are ironborn.

251
00:17:50.003 --> 00:17:53.004
            We're not subjects.
            We're not slaves.

252
00:17:53.072 --> 00:17:55.773
      We do not plow the fields
      or toil in the mine.

253
00:17:55.841 --> 00:17:57.808
          We take what is ours.

254
00:17:59.312 --> 00:18:02.162
      Your time with the wolves
      has made you weak.

255
00:18:06.318 --> 00:18:08.719
 You act as if
 I volunteered to go.

256
00:18:09.856 --> 00:18:12.073
 You gave me away.
 if you remember.

257
00:18:12.141 --> 00:18:14.608
 The day you bent the knee
 to Robert Baratheon.

258
00:18:14.677 --> 00:18:16.627
 After he crushed you.

259
00:18:16.679 --> 00:18:18.463
 Did you take
 what was yours then?

260
00:18:22.719 --> 00:18:24.102
 You gave me away!

261
00:18:25.438 --> 00:18:26.704
 Your boy!

262
00:18:27.423 --> 00:18:30.057
      Your last boy!

263
00:18:30.126 --> 00:18:33.827
 You gave me away
 like I was some dog
 you didn't want anymore.

264
00:18:33.896 --> 00:18:36.897
        And now you curse me
        because I've come home.

265
00:18:47.160 --> 00:18:50.461
 You'd have our father
 bow down to your other family?

266
00:18:50.529 --> 00:18:52.896
 I have no other family.

267
00:18:52.966 --> 00:18:54.332
               Don't you?

268
00:18:56.135 --> 00:18:58.803
 Make your choice.
 Theon. and do it quickly.

269
00:18:58.871 --> 00:19:01.405
           Our ships sail
           with or without you.

270
00:19:13.603 --> 00:19:15.168
 You won't let me
 leave this room.

271
00:19:15.237 --> 00:19:16.654
 You won't let me...

272
00:19:16.723 --> 00:19:18.088
               (SHUSHING) Keep
               your voice down.

273
00:19:21.060 --> 00:19:24.328
   Why? You think your
   father can hear me?

274
00:19:24.396 --> 00:19:26.614
 (SHOUTING) He's
 300 miles away!

275
00:19:26.682 --> 00:19:28.098
                   (SIGHS)

276
00:19:29.268 --> 00:19:32.420
             I don't intend for
             you to stay here.

277
00:19:32.488 --> 00:19:35.740
           I might be able
           to bring you into
           the castle kitchens.

278
00:19:35.808 --> 00:19:37.708
         Again. only temporary.

279
00:19:39.378 --> 00:19:41.312
 Every man who has
 tasted my cooking

280
00:19:41.380 --> 00:19:43.563
 has told me what
 a good whore I am.

281
00:19:43.632 --> 00:19:45.299
    But you wouldn't be a cook.

282
00:19:46.152 --> 00:19:48.185
      You'd pose as a scullion.

283
00:19:49.889 --> 00:19:52.072
 Scullion? What is a scullion?

284
00:19:53.275 --> 00:19:54.926
            Kitchen wench.

285
00:19:54.978 --> 00:19:56.343
 A kitchen wench?

286
00:19:56.411 --> 00:19:57.778
                Yes. but...

287
00:19:57.847 --> 00:20:01.949
 Cleaning pots?
 Is that how my lion
 wants to see me?

288
00:20:02.018 --> 00:20:04.585
            Your lion wants
            to see you alive.

289
00:20:04.654 --> 00:20:06.887
            We've come to
            a dangerous place.

290
00:20:06.956 --> 00:20:08.822
 My sister wants to hurt me.

291
00:20:08.908 --> 00:20:10.875
        She'll look for any
        weakness she can find.

292
00:20:10.943 --> 00:20:13.461
      She can't know about you.

293
00:20:13.529 --> 00:20:15.162
 I'm the weakness?

294
00:20:15.248 --> 00:20:17.181
    It's a compliment. my lady.

295
00:20:17.250 --> 00:20:20.034
 How is being
 a weakness a compliment?

296
00:20:23.505 --> 00:20:25.322
             Language can be
             a bit tricky here.

297
00:20:25.391 --> 00:20:26.523
           Oh.

298
00:20:26.593 --> 00:20:28.926
 I'm too stupid to understand.

299
00:20:28.995 --> 00:20:31.095
 The stupid foreign girl.

300
00:20:34.033 --> 00:20:36.817
 I am not a kitchen wench.

301
00:21:02.044 --> 00:21:04.678
 When will Joffrey
 and Sansa be married?

302
00:21:04.747 --> 00:21:07.398
      Soon. darling.
      when the war is over.

303
00:21:07.466 --> 00:21:09.833
 Mother says I'll have
 a new gown for the ceremony

304
00:21:09.902 --> 00:21:12.169
 and another for the feast.

305
00:21:12.221 --> 00:21:15.322
     But yours will be ivory.
     since you're the bride.

306
00:21:19.812 --> 00:21:21.929
             The Princess
             just spoke to you.

307
00:21:21.997 --> 00:21:23.597
   Pardon. Your Grace.

308
00:21:26.335 --> 00:21:29.269
    I'm sure your dress will
    be beautiful. Myrcella.

309
00:21:29.338 --> 00:21:32.089
   I'm counting the days
   until the fighting is done

310
00:21:32.158 --> 00:21:35.676
     and I can pledge
     my love to the King
     in sight of the gods.

311
00:21:39.966 --> 00:21:42.399
          Is Joffrey going to
          kill Sansa's brother?

312
00:21:45.288 --> 00:21:46.753
                 He might.

313
00:21:49.408 --> 00:21:51.091
           Would you like that?

314
00:21:52.812 --> 00:21:54.845
          No. I don't think so.

315
00:21:56.982 --> 00:21:59.983
        Even if he does.
        Sansa will do her duty.

316
00:22:02.054 --> 00:22:03.987
        Won't you. little dove?

317
00:22:20.255 --> 00:22:21.855
             (KNOCKING ON DOOR)
           (GASPS)

318
00:22:22.758 --> 00:22:24.090
    Come in.

319
00:22:27.797 --> 00:22:29.046
   Who are you?

320
00:22:29.114 --> 00:22:32.683
          I'm Shae. My Lady.
          Your new handmaiden.

321
00:22:32.752 --> 00:22:35.486
 I didn't know
 I needed a new handmaiden.

322
00:22:37.089 --> 00:22:38.522
 You're not from here.

323
00:22:38.590 --> 00:22:39.589
                      No.

324
00:22:46.099 --> 00:22:47.414
 What are you doing?

325
00:22:47.483 --> 00:22:49.232
            Waiting for you to
            tell me what to do.

326
00:22:49.301 --> 00:22:53.353
 I shouldn't have to
 tell you to do things.
 You should just do them.

327
00:22:54.089 --> 00:22:56.323
                   What things?

328
00:22:56.391 --> 00:22:58.209
 Change my linens.
 wash my clothing.

329
00:22:58.277 --> 00:23:01.528
 scrub the floor.
 empty my chamber pot.
 brush my hair.

330
00:23:10.573 --> 00:23:12.373
        No.
           You said to brush...

331
00:23:12.441 --> 00:23:13.974
      Not now.

332
00:23:17.046 --> 00:23:19.113
     Your chamber pot is empty.

333
00:23:19.949 --> 00:23:21.831
 Clean the table.

334
00:23:26.873 --> 00:23:29.807
 Have you ever been
 a handmaiden before?

335
00:23:29.876 --> 00:23:31.325
                 Yes.
     For whom?

336
00:23:31.394 --> 00:23:33.343
                Lady Zuriff.
 Lady Zuriff?

337
00:23:35.981 --> 00:23:38.081
                 Lady Zuriff.

338
00:23:38.150 --> 00:23:41.302
 There is no Lady Zuriff
 in this city.

339
00:23:41.370 --> 00:23:43.204
       She wasn't in this city.

340
00:23:43.272 --> 00:23:45.539
 I don't know how they
 did things in that city.

341
00:23:45.608 --> 00:23:48.375
 but in this city.
 handmaidens wait on ladies.

342
00:23:48.444 --> 00:23:50.010
 not the other way around.

343
00:23:50.079 --> 00:23:52.913
 And I don't have time
 to answer a thousand questions

344
00:23:52.981 --> 00:23:55.315
 and teach you
 how to do your job.

345
00:23:58.888 --> 00:24:00.137
       Do you want me to leave?

346
00:24:08.430 --> 00:24:10.080
 Just brush my hair.

347
00:24:24.580 --> 00:24:25.646
 TYRION: Oh!

348
00:24:25.714 --> 00:24:27.381
 Thank the gods.

349
00:24:27.449 --> 00:24:30.383
 I haven't had
 a proper shit in six days.

350
00:24:30.452 --> 00:24:32.669
  I've encountered
  this problem before. my lord.

351
00:24:32.738 --> 00:24:35.438
          The stresses of
          power often have this

352
00:24:36.509 --> 00:24:38.375
           insalubrious effect.

353
00:24:38.443 --> 00:24:41.712
   Two drops with water. daily.

354
00:24:41.780 --> 00:24:43.380
 Right.
 I'm so grateful to have a man

355
00:24:43.448 --> 00:24:46.349
 of your vast knowledge
 and wisdom on my side.

356
00:24:46.418 --> 00:24:47.651
        Please.

357
00:24:47.720 --> 00:24:48.886
            Thank you. my lord.

358
00:24:54.260 --> 00:24:55.910
 I can trust you.
 Pycelle. can I not?

359
00:24:55.978 --> 00:24:57.711
  Why. yes. of course. my lord.

360
00:24:57.780 --> 00:24:59.980
 These are perilous times.

361
00:25:00.049 --> 00:25:03.133
 And the crown must
 forge new alliances.

362
00:25:03.202 --> 00:25:06.570
 And these alliances
 must often be
 sealed in matrimony.

363
00:25:07.506 --> 00:25:09.573
            Matrimony. huh?

364
00:25:10.042 --> 00:25:11.741
                  Yes.

365
00:25:11.810 --> 00:25:16.112
 I'm trusting
 the council with these plans.
 but the Queen mustn't know.

366
00:25:16.182 --> 00:25:18.181
 We can't have her
 meddling in affairs

367
00:25:18.250 --> 00:25:21.117
 that could determine
 the future of the realm.
 There's too much at stake.

368
00:25:21.187 --> 00:25:24.037
     Oh. yes. yes. Indeed. yes.

369
00:25:24.106 --> 00:25:27.541
           I shall be
           silent as the grave.

370
00:25:27.610 --> 00:25:31.812
 I'm brokering an alliance
 with House Martell of Dorne.

371
00:25:31.880 --> 00:25:35.182
         Princess Myrcella will
         wed their youngest son
         when she comes of age.

372
00:25:35.267 --> 00:25:36.800
         ensuring their loyalty

373
00:25:36.869 --> 00:25:39.836
      and their army.
      should we need it.

374
00:25:39.905 --> 00:25:42.956
   Myrcella sent away to Dorne?

375
00:25:45.294 --> 00:25:47.995
 But remember.
 the Queen mustn't know.

376
00:25:48.764 --> 00:25:50.113
                   Ooh.

377
00:25:50.182 --> 00:25:52.683
      "The Queen mustn't know."

378
00:25:52.752 --> 00:25:56.370
           I love conversations
           that begin this way.

379
00:25:56.438 --> 00:25:59.239
 I plan to marry
 Princess Myrcella off

380
00:25:59.308 --> 00:26:00.691
 to Theon Greyjoy.

381
00:26:02.361 --> 00:26:04.962
                Theon Greyjoy?

382
00:26:05.030 --> 00:26:07.431
           Forgive me. my lord.
           but how?

383
00:26:07.499 --> 00:26:10.033
          He grew up
          a ward of Winterfell.

384
00:26:10.102 --> 00:26:11.535
 He fights for Robb Stark.

385
00:26:11.604 --> 00:26:12.970
    Precisely.

386
00:26:13.022 --> 00:26:15.489
 Theon's father
 loathes the Starks

387
00:26:15.557 --> 00:26:18.725
 and will convince
 the boy to come to our side.

388
00:26:18.793 --> 00:26:21.562
  Greyjoy can destroy
  the Northern army from within

389
00:26:21.630 --> 00:26:24.264
            and we can have
            his father's ships.

390
00:26:24.332 --> 00:26:26.867
 But remember.
 you must tell no one.

391
00:26:27.653 --> 00:26:30.804
              Tell no one what?

392
00:26:30.872 --> 00:26:33.957
 I plan to wed
 Princess Myrcella
 to Robin Arryn of the Vale.

393
00:26:35.828 --> 00:26:38.895
 Lysa is not fond of me.

394
00:26:38.965 --> 00:26:41.749
 But perhaps
 the promise of a royal match

395
00:26:41.817 --> 00:26:44.885
 will convince her to
 let bygones be bygones.

396
00:26:44.953 --> 00:26:48.889
      She imprisoned you.
      She tried to execute you.

397
00:26:48.957 --> 00:26:52.225
            And you offer
            her son a princess?

398
00:26:52.294 --> 00:26:55.729
 For men in our position.
 holding grudges can be

399
00:26:55.797 --> 00:26:58.315
 an encumbrance.
 don't you think?

400
00:26:58.384 --> 00:27:01.785
      And I suppose you want me
      to broker this agreement?

401
00:27:01.853 --> 00:27:03.320
      Who better?

402
00:27:07.476 --> 00:27:11.728
             Yes. I could sing
             this song to Lysa.
             if I cared to.

403
00:27:13.398 --> 00:27:14.414
           What's in it for me?

404
00:27:16.702 --> 00:27:20.504
 The gratitude of
 the people of Westeros
 for helping to end this war.

405
00:27:20.573 --> 00:27:24.808
 the adoration of the King
 for bringing the Vale
 back into the fold...

406
00:27:26.545 --> 00:27:28.378
       and Harrenhal.

407
00:27:28.447 --> 00:27:30.514
           Harrenhal is cursed.

408
00:27:30.582 --> 00:27:32.749
 Never took you for
 a superstitious man.

409
00:27:32.818 --> 00:27:36.486
 By all means.
 tear it down and rebuild.
 You'll be able to afford it.

410
00:27:36.555 --> 00:27:39.389
 I plan to make you
 Lord of the Riverlands.

411
00:27:41.310 --> 00:27:42.709
          With a single stroke.
          you'd make me

412
00:27:42.778 --> 00:27:44.294
            one of the greatest
            lords in the realm.

413
00:27:44.363 --> 00:27:47.330
 You served my family well
 in the matter of
 the succession.

414
00:27:47.399 --> 00:27:50.451
    So did Janos Slynt.
    and he was given Harrenhal.
    too.

415
00:27:50.536 --> 00:27:52.970
    Until you snatched it away.

416
00:27:53.038 --> 00:27:55.772
 I need you to
 deliver Lysa Arryn.

417
00:27:55.841 --> 00:27:57.874
 I didn't need Janos Slynt.

418
00:28:00.946 --> 00:28:02.679
 It's settled. then?

419
00:28:05.000 --> 00:28:06.116
          Good.

420
00:28:08.837 --> 00:28:10.137
 Oh. And remember...

421
00:28:10.205 --> 00:28:12.205
 The Queen mustn't know.

422
00:28:24.570 --> 00:28:26.136
            (BREATHING HEAVILY)

423
00:28:51.413 --> 00:28:52.879
              That must hurt.

424
00:28:53.449 --> 00:28:54.781
    (GROANS)

425
00:29:03.558 --> 00:29:04.724
           What?

426
00:29:06.996 --> 00:29:08.311
         What is it?

427
00:29:09.097 --> 00:29:10.130
       (SCOFFS)

428
00:29:10.199 --> 00:29:12.299
 A member of the Kingsguard?

429
00:29:14.002 --> 00:29:16.152
 As if I wasn't
 humiliated enough already.

430
00:29:16.555 --> 00:29:18.455
            (SIGHS)

431
00:29:18.523 --> 00:29:21.925
         Brienne is a very
         capable warrior.

432
00:29:23.829 --> 00:29:25.846
       And she's devoted to me.

433
00:29:28.083 --> 00:29:29.233
           You're jealous.

434
00:29:31.203 --> 00:29:32.352
          Jealous?

435
00:29:32.421 --> 00:29:34.388
 Of Brienne the Beauty?

436
00:29:35.090 --> 00:29:36.857
 Don't make me laugh.

437
00:29:38.494 --> 00:29:40.110
        I'll make it up to you.

438
00:29:40.179 --> 00:29:41.728
        No. Your Grace.

439
00:29:42.897 --> 00:29:44.014
      Not tonight.

440
00:29:45.651 --> 00:29:48.368
 There's another Tyrell
 who requires your attention.

441
00:29:48.437 --> 00:29:52.305
 You didn't win my
 father's support
 or his army on charm alone.

442
00:30:05.688 --> 00:30:09.556
 Your vassals are starting
 to snigger behind your back.

443
00:30:09.625 --> 00:30:12.275
 Brides aren't usually virgins
 two weeks after
 their wedding night.

444
00:30:12.344 --> 00:30:14.294
           (SCOFFS) And
           Margaery's a virgin?

445
00:30:14.929 --> 00:30:16.296
        Officially.

446
00:30:17.966 --> 00:30:19.966
 Shall I bring her to you?

447
00:30:46.912 --> 00:30:50.647
 I should warn you.
 I've had quite a bit of wine.

448
00:30:50.716 --> 00:30:52.916
              As is your right.
              You are a king.

449
00:30:55.370 --> 00:30:57.637
 You look very beautiful.

450
00:30:57.706 --> 00:30:59.189
         Thank you. Your Grace.

451
00:31:00.092 --> 00:31:01.291
            It's a lovely gown.

452
00:31:01.360 --> 00:31:02.526
 You think so?

453
00:31:03.796 --> 00:31:05.829
             I can't decide how
             I like it better.

454
00:31:05.898 --> 00:31:07.164
                   This way.

455
00:31:07.900 --> 00:31:10.466
                   or this way.

456
00:31:17.192 --> 00:31:18.792
 You certainly don't need it.

457
00:31:20.395 --> 00:31:25.331
 Although. some say
 the beauty most desired

458
00:31:25.400 --> 00:31:27.383
 is the beauty concealed.

459
00:31:44.052 --> 00:31:46.185
 Must be the wine.

460
00:31:46.254 --> 00:31:48.104
                Here. let me.

461
00:32:02.854 --> 00:32:05.088
        (SHUDDERS)

462
00:32:08.594 --> 00:32:09.576
     I'm sorry.

463
00:32:11.163 --> 00:32:13.563
         Do you want my brother
         to come in and help?

464
00:32:16.201 --> 00:32:17.200
          What?

465
00:32:17.269 --> 00:32:18.268
      He could get you started.

466
00:32:18.337 --> 00:32:19.769
       I know he wouldn't mind.

467
00:32:19.838 --> 00:32:22.088
   Or I can turn over
   and you can pretend I'm him.

468
00:32:24.660 --> 00:32:26.776
 I don't know what
 you're talking about.

469
00:32:32.418 --> 00:32:35.585
          There's no need
          for us to play games.

470
00:32:35.654 --> 00:32:38.604
      Save your lies for court.
      You're going to
      need a lot of them.

471
00:32:57.076 --> 00:33:02.145
    Your enemies
    aren't happy about us.
    They want to tear us apart.

472
00:33:02.214 --> 00:33:04.481
  And the best way to stop them

473
00:33:05.550 --> 00:33:07.284
            is to put your baby

474
00:33:08.553 --> 00:33:10.053
                   in my belly.

475
00:33:13.859 --> 00:33:16.626
        We can try again later.

476
00:33:16.695 --> 00:33:20.096
    You decide how
    you want to do it.
    with me. with me and Loras.

477
00:33:20.165 --> 00:33:22.031
         however else you like.

478
00:33:25.353 --> 00:33:27.353
       Whatever you need to do.

479
00:33:29.891 --> 00:33:32.024
                You are a king.

480
00:33:41.519 --> 00:33:43.086
 CERSEI: You monster.

481
00:33:44.156 --> 00:33:46.022
 Myrcella is my only daughter.

482
00:33:46.091 --> 00:33:48.758
 Do you really think
 I'll let you sell her
 like a common whore?

483
00:33:48.827 --> 00:33:51.962
         Myrcella's a princess.
         Some would say she
         was born for this.

484
00:33:52.030 --> 00:33:53.897
 I will not let you
 ship her off to Dorne

485
00:33:53.965 --> 00:33:55.799
 as I was shipped off
 to Robert Baratheon.

486
00:33:55.867 --> 00:33:58.384
      Dorne is
      the safest place for her.

487
00:33:58.453 --> 00:34:01.655
 Are you mad?
 The Martells loathe us.

488
00:34:01.723 --> 00:34:03.990
           That's why we
           need to seduce them.

489
00:34:04.076 --> 00:34:07.594
       We're going to need
       their support in the war
       your son started.

490
00:34:07.662 --> 00:34:08.811
 She'll be a hostage.

491
00:34:08.881 --> 00:34:09.946
                      A guest.

492
00:34:10.916 --> 00:34:13.149
 You won't get away with this.

493
00:34:13.218 --> 00:34:16.486
 You think the piece of
 paper Father gave you
 keeps you safe.

494
00:34:19.575 --> 00:34:21.508
 Ned Stark had
 a piece of paper. too.

495
00:34:24.479 --> 00:34:26.346
             It's done. Cersei.
            No.

496
00:34:27.365 --> 00:34:28.598
            You cannot stop it.

497
00:34:28.667 --> 00:34:29.866
         No!

498
00:34:33.371 --> 00:34:36.373
          Just how safe do
          you think Myrcella is
          if this city falls?

499
00:34:36.441 --> 00:34:40.377
  Do you want to see her raped.
  butchered like
  the Targaryen children?

500
00:34:40.446 --> 00:34:42.294
               Make no mistake.

501
00:34:42.363 --> 00:34:44.831
  They'll mount her
  pretty little head on a spike
  right beside yours.

502
00:34:44.900 --> 00:34:46.800
 Get out! Get out!

503
00:35:49.481 --> 00:35:52.148
    Theon of the House Greyjoy.

504
00:35:52.217 --> 00:35:55.302
      you would this day
      consecrate your
      faith to the Drowned God?

505
00:36:03.861 --> 00:36:04.994
      I would.

506
00:36:05.063 --> 00:36:06.128
                        Kneel.

507
00:36:09.668 --> 00:36:11.000
         Let Theon.
         your servant.

508
00:36:11.069 --> 00:36:13.836
      be born again from
      the sea as you were.

509
00:36:14.806 --> 00:36:16.639
           Bless him with salt.

510
00:36:19.444 --> 00:36:21.344
          Bless him with stone.

511
00:36:22.364 --> 00:36:23.813
          Bless him with steel.

512
00:36:29.421 --> 00:36:31.287
 What is dead may never die.

513
00:36:31.339 --> 00:36:33.439
    What is dead may never die.

514
00:36:35.010 --> 00:36:38.211
           But rises again
           harder and stronger.

515
00:36:39.380 --> 00:36:40.714
                  Stand.

516
00:37:01.336 --> 00:37:02.468
         (DOG BARKING)

517
00:37:07.042 --> 00:37:09.643
    (FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

518
00:37:09.711 --> 00:37:12.579
   I don't appreciate
   being made a fool of. dwarf.

519
00:37:13.915 --> 00:37:15.465
            If Myrcella marries
            the Martell boy.

520
00:37:15.534 --> 00:37:18.118
    she can't very well
    marry Robin Arryn. can she?

521
00:37:18.186 --> 00:37:21.087
    No. afraid not.
    Sorry about that.

522
00:37:21.156 --> 00:37:23.056
                 And Harrenhal.

523
00:37:23.125 --> 00:37:26.058
         I suppose that's
         off the table as well.

524
00:37:26.144 --> 00:37:29.712
 Yes. I fear so.
 Sorry about that. too.

525
00:37:29.781 --> 00:37:32.782
           Leave me out of
           your next deception.

526
00:37:32.850 --> 00:37:34.200
 That's a shame.

527
00:37:34.269 --> 00:37:37.470
 You were to be
 the centerpiece of
 my next deception.

528
00:37:37.539 --> 00:37:40.856
 My brother Jaime rots
 in a northern stockade.

529
00:37:40.925 --> 00:37:44.360
 I would see him released.
 That's where you come in.

530
00:37:44.412 --> 00:37:46.880
        Robb Stark will never
        release the Kingslayer.

531
00:37:46.965 --> 00:37:49.933
 No. he won't.
 But his mother might.

532
00:37:51.302 --> 00:37:53.719
 How would you like to see
 your beloved Cat again?

533
00:37:54.389 --> 00:37:55.821
    (FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

534
00:37:57.259 --> 00:37:59.558
 Find him?
       Oh. aye.

535
00:37:59.627 --> 00:38:01.160
            And he has company.

536
00:38:02.864 --> 00:38:05.781
      Filthy old stoat.
      Almost hate to interrupt.

537
00:38:05.850 --> 00:38:07.016
    No. you don't.

538
00:38:07.686 --> 00:38:08.918
 No. I don't.

539
00:38:13.174 --> 00:38:14.256
 (DOOR SLAMS OPEN)
             (GASPS)

540
00:38:16.077 --> 00:38:18.510
   What is the meaning of this?

541
00:38:18.580 --> 00:38:20.830
            No. please. please.

542
00:38:20.899 --> 00:38:23.032
 You disappoint me.
 Grand Maester.

543
00:38:23.101 --> 00:38:25.284
       I am your loyal servant.

544
00:38:25.353 --> 00:38:27.253
 So loyal that
 you told the Queen

545
00:38:27.321 --> 00:38:29.154
 about my plans to
 send Myrcella to Dorne.

546
00:38:29.223 --> 00:38:31.123
                No! Never!

547
00:38:31.192 --> 00:38:33.543
            It's a falsehood.
            I swear it.

548
00:38:33.612 --> 00:38:35.094
                  It wasn't me.

549
00:38:36.247 --> 00:38:37.363
                Ah. Varys.

550
00:38:37.432 --> 00:38:40.182
       It was Varys the Spider.

551
00:38:40.251 --> 00:38:44.920
 See. I told Varys that
 I was giving
 the Princess to the Greyjoys.

552
00:38:44.989 --> 00:38:49.242
 I told Littlefinger
 that I planned to
 wed her to Robin Arryn.

553
00:38:49.310 --> 00:38:52.145
 I told no one
 that I was offering
 her to the Dornish.

554
00:38:53.281 --> 00:38:54.947
     No one but you.

555
00:38:55.033 --> 00:38:57.483
              The eunuch has
              spies everywhere.

556
00:38:57.552 --> 00:38:59.619
 Cut off his manhood
 and feed it to the goats.

557
00:38:59.687 --> 00:39:01.054
                    No. no. no.

558
00:39:01.122 --> 00:39:02.455
   There are no goats. halfman.

559
00:39:02.523 --> 00:39:03.823
   Well. make do.

560
00:39:03.891 --> 00:39:06.392
           (PYCELLE WHIMPERING)

561
00:39:06.461 --> 00:39:08.811
 How long have you been
 spying for my sister?

562
00:39:08.880 --> 00:39:11.748
     All I did.
     I did for House Lannister.

563
00:39:11.800 --> 00:39:14.084
     Always.
     Your lord father. ask him.

564
00:39:14.136 --> 00:39:17.653
   I've always been his servant
   since the days
   of the Mad King.

565
00:39:19.691 --> 00:39:20.723
 I don't like his beard.

566
00:39:20.792 --> 00:39:22.175
                    What?

567
00:39:22.244 --> 00:39:24.877
     What? No. No.

568
00:39:25.781 --> 00:39:28.181
              (WHIMPERING)

569
00:39:28.249 --> 00:39:30.916
 How many Hands have
 you betrayed. Pycelle?

570
00:39:30.986 --> 00:39:33.019
 Eddard Stark? Jon Arryn?

571
00:39:33.087 --> 00:39:35.021
           Lord Arryn. he knew.

572
00:39:35.090 --> 00:39:38.024
           (STAMMERING)
           He knew the truth
           about the Queen.

573
00:39:38.092 --> 00:39:43.279
       And...he planned to act.
       to tell King Robert.

574
00:39:43.331 --> 00:39:44.647
 So you poisoned him?

575
00:39:45.267 --> 00:39:47.066
                 No. Never.

576
00:39:47.135 --> 00:39:49.835
 But you let him die.
 made sure he succumbed.

577
00:39:49.921 --> 00:39:52.571
     Lannister...
     I always served Lannister.

578
00:39:52.640 --> 00:39:55.324
 Get him out of my sight.
 Throw him in one
 of the black cells.

579
00:39:55.393 --> 00:39:57.126
             No. No. no. no.
             No. please.

580
00:39:57.195 --> 00:39:59.111
 Don't!
 You can't do this to me!

581
00:40:00.681 --> 00:40:01.997
       For your trouble.

582
00:40:03.185 --> 00:40:04.750
 (PYCELLE SHOUTING)

583
00:40:26.758 --> 00:40:29.042
 You'll be pleased to
 know our mutual friend

584
00:40:29.127 --> 00:40:32.027
 is doing quite well in
 Lady Sansa's service.

585
00:40:32.930 --> 00:40:35.831
  Good. One of my better ideas.

586
00:40:35.900 --> 00:40:40.202
 And it seems the Grand Maester
 has found his way
 into a black cell?

587
00:40:42.724 --> 00:40:44.857
 Well played. My Lord Hand.

588
00:40:46.310 --> 00:40:48.645
 But should I be worried?

589
00:40:48.713 --> 00:40:50.913
 Janos Slynt. Pycelle...

590
00:40:50.982 --> 00:40:53.533
 The Small Council
 grows smaller every day.

591
00:40:53.601 --> 00:40:57.036
 The Council has a reputation
 for serving past Hands poorly.

592
00:40:57.105 --> 00:40:59.772
        I don't mean to follow
        Ned Stark to the grave.

593
00:41:00.859 --> 00:41:03.492
 Power is
 a curious thing. my lord.

594
00:41:04.996 --> 00:41:06.579
 Are you fond of riddles?

595
00:41:06.647 --> 00:41:08.681
   Why. am I about to hear one?

596
00:41:08.749 --> 00:41:10.950
 Three great men sit in a room.

597
00:41:11.018 --> 00:41:13.853
 A king.
 a priest and a rich man.

598
00:41:13.921 --> 00:41:16.639
 Between them stands
 a common sellsword.

599
00:41:16.707 --> 00:41:20.810
 Each great man
 bids the sellsword
 kill the other two.

600
00:41:20.879 --> 00:41:23.213
 Who lives. who dies?

601
00:41:24.132 --> 00:41:25.698
      Depends on the sellsword.

602
00:41:25.766 --> 00:41:29.986
 Does it? He has neither crown
 nor gold nor
 favor with the gods.

603
00:41:30.054 --> 00:41:32.238
   He has a sword.
   the power of life and death.

604
00:41:32.324 --> 00:41:34.657
 But if it's
 swordsmen who rule.

605
00:41:34.726 --> 00:41:37.476
 why do we pretend
 kings hold all the power?

606
00:41:37.545 --> 00:41:42.431
 When Ned Stark lost his head.
 who was truly responsible?

607
00:41:42.501 --> 00:41:46.352
 Joffrey? The executioner?
 Or something else?

608
00:41:46.421 --> 00:41:48.621
          I've decided
          I don't like riddles.

609
00:41:51.743 --> 00:41:55.344
 Power resides where
 men believe it resides.

610
00:41:56.781 --> 00:42:00.933
 It's a trick.
 a shadow on the wall.

611
00:42:01.002 --> 00:42:06.989
 And a very small man
 can cast a very large shadow.

612
00:42:15.182 --> 00:42:16.816
 (HORSE WHINNIES)

613
00:42:18.303 --> 00:42:20.136
 (SNORING)

614
00:42:30.097 --> 00:42:31.531
 (DOOR OPENS)

615
00:42:47.315 --> 00:42:49.265
 You should be sleeping.

616
00:42:50.268 --> 00:42:53.402
 Tomorrow's a long march.

617
00:42:53.471 --> 00:42:55.838
 Thirty miles.
 if it don't piss on us.

618
00:42:57.475 --> 00:42:58.708
      I can't sleep.

619
00:43:03.631 --> 00:43:05.514
        I don't like the taste.

620
00:43:06.034 --> 00:43:07.400
    (CHUCKLES)

621
00:43:08.503 --> 00:43:09.735
     (GRUNTS)

622
00:43:11.272 --> 00:43:14.690
 You don't drink it for
 the flavor. to be honest.

623
00:43:22.733 --> 00:43:24.050
            What?

624
00:43:25.386 --> 00:43:27.453
              How do you sleep?

625
00:43:27.522 --> 00:43:29.888
 Same as most men. I think.

626
00:43:29.957 --> 00:43:32.341
        But you've seen things.

627
00:43:33.778 --> 00:43:35.411
               horrible things.

628
00:43:36.514 --> 00:43:37.546
 Aye.

629
00:43:39.017 --> 00:43:41.534
 I've seen some
 pretty things. too.

630
00:43:41.602 --> 00:43:43.536
 but not nearly so many.

631
00:43:45.389 --> 00:43:47.523
   How do you sleep when you...

632
00:43:49.427 --> 00:43:53.195
           When you have those
           things in your head?

633
00:43:55.967 --> 00:43:57.450
 You didn't see that.

634
00:43:58.770 --> 00:44:00.235
   I made damn sure.

635
00:44:00.305 --> 00:44:02.438
           I close my eyes and
           I see them up there.

636
00:44:04.108 --> 00:44:05.574
                    All of them

637
00:44:06.311 --> 00:44:07.976
                standing there.

638
00:44:09.213 --> 00:44:10.613
                    Joffrey.

639
00:44:12.784 --> 00:44:15.284
               the Queen and...

640
00:44:17.087 --> 00:44:18.554
                 and my sister.

641
00:44:27.649 --> 00:44:31.667
 You know. we've got
 something in common.
 me and you.

642
00:44:31.736 --> 00:44:33.152
 You know that?

643
00:44:34.271 --> 00:44:35.971
      I must have been

644
00:44:37.041 --> 00:44:39.441
    a couple of years
    older than you.

645
00:44:41.378 --> 00:44:43.612
 I saw my brother
 stabbed through the heart

646
00:44:43.664 --> 00:44:45.964
 right on our doorstep.

647
00:44:46.033 --> 00:44:49.502
 He weren't much of a villain
 what skewered him.

648
00:44:49.570 --> 00:44:51.670
 Willem. the lad's name was.

649
00:44:53.608 --> 00:44:56.142
 He ran off before
 anyone could spit.

650
00:44:57.245 --> 00:44:59.211
 And I just stood there.

651
00:45:00.314 --> 00:45:02.331
 watching my brother die.

652
00:45:03.835 --> 00:45:07.019
 Here's the funny part.

653
00:45:07.088 --> 00:45:09.972
 I can't picture my
 brother's face anymore.

654
00:45:10.975 --> 00:45:12.858
 But Willem.

655
00:45:12.927 --> 00:45:14.994
 oh. he was a nice-looking boy.

656
00:45:17.398 --> 00:45:20.967
 He had good white teeth.
 blue eyes.

657
00:45:22.236 --> 00:45:25.338
 one of those dimpled
 chins all the girls like.

658
00:45:28.042 --> 00:45:31.010
 I would think about him
 when I was working.

659
00:45:31.079 --> 00:45:34.113
 when I was drinking.
 when I was having a shit.

660
00:45:35.316 --> 00:45:37.350
 It got to the point

661
00:45:37.418 --> 00:45:40.619
 where I would say
 his name every night
 before I went to bed.

662
00:45:40.688 --> 00:45:42.521
 Willem. Willem.

663
00:45:43.257 --> 00:45:44.556
 Willem.

664
00:45:45.994 --> 00:45:47.693
    A prayer almost.

665
00:45:49.897 --> 00:45:51.497
 Well. one day.

666
00:45:53.734 --> 00:45:56.302
 Willem came
 riding back into town.

667
00:46:00.308 --> 00:46:05.777
 I buried an ax so
 deep into Willem's skull
 they had to bury him with it.

668
00:46:09.250 --> 00:46:11.550
 Willem's horse
 got me to the Wall

669
00:46:11.618 --> 00:46:13.853
 and I've been
 wearing black ever since.

670
00:46:19.827 --> 00:46:22.477
 That'll help you sleep. eh?
 (CHUCKLES)

671
00:46:25.449 --> 00:46:26.682
         (HORN SOUNDS)

672
00:46:26.751 --> 00:46:27.916
         (MEN SHOUTING)

673
00:46:29.270 --> 00:46:30.386
        Ho!

674
00:46:30.455 --> 00:46:33.539
 Get up.
 you lazy sons of whores!

675
00:46:33.608 --> 00:46:35.274
 Arm yourselves.

676
00:46:36.444 --> 00:46:38.561
            GENDRY: Get up.
 ARYA: Get up.

677
00:46:38.630 --> 00:46:40.196
             Keep out of sight.
             both of you.

678
00:46:40.265 --> 00:46:41.597
   No. I'm not afraid.
 I can fight.

679
00:46:41.666 --> 00:46:43.999
             Keep out of sight.

680
00:46:44.068 --> 00:46:46.569
   If things go wrong. you run.

681
00:46:46.638 --> 00:46:50.573
           Do you hear me?
           You run along north
           and don't look back.

682
00:46:52.110 --> 00:46:55.728
 Hey. there's men out there
 who want to fuck your corpses.

683
00:46:55.797 --> 00:46:57.663
                  Outside. now!

684
00:46:59.783 --> 00:47:01.684
   MAN: Come on. move. move!

685
00:47:01.752 --> 00:47:03.218
        (HORSE WHINNIES)

686
00:47:03.287 --> 00:47:04.720
 Gold cloaks!

687
00:47:07.625 --> 00:47:08.891
         (SHOUTING)

688
00:47:10.461 --> 00:47:12.394
 Everyone out!

689
00:47:12.463 --> 00:47:13.796
           (SHOUTING)

690
00:47:16.884 --> 00:47:20.085
 Hey. you! Open the damn cage!

691
00:47:23.925 --> 00:47:25.474
     Where's the bastard. crow?

692
00:47:25.543 --> 00:47:27.993
 Got more than
 a few bastards here.
 Who's asking?

693
00:47:28.062 --> 00:47:31.196
          Ser Amory Lorch.
          sworn bannerman to
          Lord Tywin Lannister.

694
00:47:31.266 --> 00:47:35.134
     These men from the capital
     requested our assistance.

695
00:47:35.202 --> 00:47:37.436
          Drop your weapons in
          the name of the King.

696
00:47:37.505 --> 00:47:39.372
 Now. which king would that be?

697
00:47:39.440 --> 00:47:41.840
      This is your last chance.

698
00:47:41.909 --> 00:47:46.211
   In the name of King Joffrey.
   drop your weapons.

699
00:47:49.784 --> 00:47:51.917
 I don't think I will.

700
00:47:51.986 --> 00:47:53.252
                   So be it.

701
00:47:53.888 --> 00:47:54.953
            (GRUNTS)

702
00:47:56.857 --> 00:48:00.125
 I always hated crossbows.
 Take too long to load.

703
00:48:18.079 --> 00:48:19.244
             (GROANS)

704
00:48:25.669 --> 00:48:27.203
       (GURGLES)

705
00:48:38.299 --> 00:48:40.366
 JAQEN: Boy. come here. Boy!

706
00:48:40.434 --> 00:48:42.134
 Sweet boy. help us.

707
00:48:42.203 --> 00:48:43.869
 Come back here!

708
00:48:43.937 --> 00:48:45.087
      Help us. boy!

709
00:48:46.040 --> 00:48:47.489
 (SHOUTING)

710
00:48:49.060 --> 00:48:51.544
 A man can fight! Free us!

711
00:48:58.669 --> 00:49:00.535
 Quick. give it to me.

712
00:49:01.905 --> 00:49:03.505
 Give me the ax. Give me that.

713
00:49:13.333 --> 00:49:14.934
 MAN: Put them on the wagon!

714
00:49:15.870 --> 00:49:17.335
 There's more here. Come on.

715
00:49:17.404 --> 00:49:18.503
       (GRUNTS)

716
00:49:18.573 --> 00:49:19.939
          (PANTING)

717
00:49:20.007 --> 00:49:21.339
                (CHUCKLES)

718
00:49:22.777 --> 00:49:24.643
          What do we have here?

719
00:49:26.180 --> 00:49:28.180
           No!

720
00:49:28.248 --> 00:49:30.348
    That's a fine little blade.

721
00:49:32.153 --> 00:49:33.652
              Maybe I'll pick
              my teeth with it.

722
00:49:33.721 --> 00:49:35.387
       I yield! I yield!

723
00:49:35.456 --> 00:49:37.689
 AMORY: Round up any survivors.

724
00:49:37.759 --> 00:49:39.892
 We'll take them
 back to Harrenhal.

725
00:49:39.961 --> 00:49:42.594
         You heard him.
         You're coming with us.

726
00:49:43.631 --> 00:49:44.997
     I yield!

727
00:49:47.651 --> 00:49:49.051
                   (WHIMPERING)

728
00:49:50.621 --> 00:49:51.786
                          Help!

729
00:49:51.855 --> 00:49:53.288
                  Help me!

730
00:49:57.661 --> 00:49:59.261
 Something wrong
 with your leg. boy?

731
00:49:59.330 --> 00:50:01.063
                Look at it.

732
00:50:09.240 --> 00:50:10.939
 Can you walk?

733
00:50:11.008 --> 00:50:12.974
       No. You got to carry me.

734
00:50:14.412 --> 00:50:15.844
        All right.

735
00:50:24.188 --> 00:50:25.187
                 (COUGHING)

736
00:50:30.261 --> 00:50:32.310
 "Carry him." he says. (LAUGHS)

737
00:50:41.272 --> 00:50:43.639
        We're looking for
        a bastard named Gendry.

738
00:50:44.442 --> 00:50:46.542
                    Give him up

739
00:50:46.611 --> 00:50:48.711
 or I'll start taking eyeballs.

740
00:51:01.692 --> 00:51:02.824
     You want Gendry?

741
00:51:06.898 --> 00:51:08.663
   You already got him.

742
00:51:12.937 --> 00:51:14.636
 He loved that helmet.

742
00:51:15.305 --> 00:52:15.322
